From a0b1c2d3e4f5a6b7c8d9e0f1a2b3c4d5e6f7a8b9 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: ret2ldz <ret2ldz@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Sun, 13 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] Florida: perfetto-skip

Skip threads whose name starts with `perfetto_hprof_` during thread
enumeration in `_gum_process_enumerate_threads()`. These threads are
spawned by the Android runtime's perfetto heap profiler and are a known
crash source — gum's thread enumeration segfaults on some devices when
it tries to introspect perfetto threads that are in the middle of
munmap-ing their own stack.

phantom-frida shipped this as a "stability fix" but their version was
broken: it used `goto skip;` without defining a `skip:` label (compile
error) and a typo `perfetto_hprob_` instead of `perfetto_hprof_` (the
check would never match anything). This version uses a clean
short-circuit `&&` so no label is needed, and uses `strncmp` with the
correct 15-char prefix length (`perfetto_hprof_` is 15 chars including
the trailing underscore, but thread names usually carry a numeric suffix
like `perfetto_hprof_12345` so prefix match is what we want).

Merged (with bug fixes) from
https://github.com/TheQmaks/phantom-frida (get_stability_patches_17).

---
 gum/backend-linux/gumprocess-linux.c | 3 ++-
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/gum/backend-linux/gumprocess-linux.c b/gum/backend-linux/gumprocess-linux.c
index f922da5..6c1ac71 100644
--- a/gum/backend-linux/gumprocess-linux.c
+++ b/gum/backend-linux/gumprocess-linux.c
@@ -1139,7 +1139,8 @@ _gum_process_enumerate_threads (GumFoundThreadFunc func,

     entry = &g_array_index (entries, GumThreadDetails, i);

-    if (gum_fill_thread_details (entry, flags))
+    if (gum_fill_thread_details (entry, flags) &&
+        !(entry->name != NULL && strncmp (entry->name, "perfetto_hprof_", 15) == 0))
       carry_on = func (entry, user_data);

     g_free ((gpointer) entry->name);
